  "texts": [
    "The method is mainly composed of two crucial steps:",
    "First, define the node (i.e.",
    "genes and phenotypes) feature and construct the topology graph by the k-Nearest Neighbors (k-NN) algorithm to explore the most relevant and helpful information for GPAs.",
    "As shown in the Supplementary Table 2, we crawled and constructed a balanced dataset, involving in 23558 GPA entries, 12187 genes, and 32 traits.",
    "With the assumption that the genes with similar functions are more likely to be associated with similar phenotypes, we calculated the semantic similarity based on the descriptions of genes and phenotypes, and obtained two similarity matrixes: gene semantic similarity matrix GSSMðg i; g j Þ and phenotype semantic similarity matrix PSSMðp i; p j Þ."
